Bevacizumab has been studied in the context of glioblastoma, but no specific study directly examines its use in this cancer type. However, a review on tumor-agnostic therapies (CITATIONS:
- Tumor-Agnostic Therapies Reshaping Cancer Care
) and another on advanced molecular diagnostic tools (CITATIONS:
- Advanced molecular diagnostic tools: A step closer to precision medicine in neuro-oncology
) may provide some insights into the broader context of anti-VEGF therapies in cancer treatment.

There is limited information available on specific studies assessing motor neuron disease progression and riluzole or edaravone therapy. However, a survey of service needs to embed genome sequencing for motor neuron disease in neurology in the English National Health Service (CITATIONS:
- Howard J, Bekker HL, McDermott CJ, McNeill A, Journal of medical genetics (2024-Jun-20)
) highlights the importance of understanding genetic factors in MND.
